{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_83","type":"agent_message","text":"The pattern is clearer now: `wildfly-common` carries a substitution for the old class `org.graalvm.compiler.api.directives.GraalDirectives`. On GraalVM 25.0.3 that class is no longer naturally available, which explains why someone previously tried to paper over it with `org.graalvm.compiler:compiler:23.0.2`. I’m checking the installed GraalVM modules next so I can choose the least-wrong compatibility fix."}}
